# .claudeignore - Custom Exclusions for Code Indexing
#
# This file works like .gitignore but is specifically for controlling
# what gets indexed into semantic memory. Use this for:
#
# - Secrets and credentials that should NEVER be indexed
# - Personal notes and TODOs that shouldn't pollute the knowledge graph
# - Test outputs and coverage reports that vary by developer
# - Debug artifacts and temporary files
# - Large generated files not caught by .gitignore
#
# Syntax is identical to .gitignore:
# - Lines starting with # are comments
# - * matches any string (single level)
# - ** matches any string including directory separators
# - / at end denotes a directory
# - / at start makes pattern relative to project root
# - ! negates a pattern (includes previously excluded files)
#
# Note: .gitignore patterns are automatically respected via the universal defaults.
# This file is for ADDITIONAL exclusions specific to indexing.

